claim: Flublok ensures identical antigenic match with WHO- and FDA-selected flu strains.
explanation: A table presenting clinical outcomes comparing two vaccine groups (N=279,400 vs. N=395,852). Outcomes include incidence of PCR-confirmed influenza (overall, type A, type B), hospitalizations for PCR-confirmed influenza, community-acquired pneumonia, and cardiorespiratory events, with columns for unadjusted rate ratio, hazard ratio (95% CI), effectiveness (95% CI), and P values. The table presents comparative effectiveness and clinical outcome data for two vaccine groups but contains no information on antigenic matching or alignment with WHO- or FDA-selected influenza strains; it does not support the claim.
